<TITLE> 4 senior cricketers' contracts scaled down by six months </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 5 (bdnews24.com) - The contracts of four senior cricketers have been scaled down by sixth months from one year, the Bangladesh Cricket Board (BCB) announced Wednesday in its 22-member contractual players' list. They are opener Javed Omar, spinner Mohammad Rafique, opener Shahriar Nafees and wicketkeeper Khaled Mashud, who now have been included in the list of six months contracts along with seven other cricketers. The contracts of Abdur Razzak, Saqib Al Hasan, Syed Rasel, Mushfiqur Rahim, and Shahadat Hossain have been upgraded to one year from six months, while Mohammad Ashraful, Mashrafee Bin Mortaza, Habibul Bashar and Aftab Ahmed enjoy their previous full-year contracts. Opener Tamim Iqbal has been upgraded to six months from the rookie contract. Opener Junaed Siddique and all-rounder Mahmudullah Riyad have been included in the new payroll for six months under rookie contracts, but pacer Tapash Kumar Baishya has been excluded. All contracts will be effective from December 1. One year contracts: Mohammad Ashraful, Masrafee Bin Mortaza, Habibul Bashar, Aftab Ahmed, Shahadat Hossain, Abdur Razzak, Syed Rasel, Saqib Al Hasan, Mushfiqur Rahim. Sixth month contracts: Tamim Iqbal, Shahriar Nafees, Khaled Mashud, Javed Omar, Mohammad Rafique, Tushar Imran, Farhad Reza, Mehrab Hossain Junior, Enamul Haque Junior, Nazmul Hossain and Rajin Salah. Rookie contracts: Mahmudullah Raiad and Junaed Siddique. b
